<p>
    For each function given below,
    identify its fundamental algebraic structure.
    In particular, is the given function a sum,
    product, quotient, or composition of basic functions?  
    Once you identify the correct algebraic structure, you'll be prompted to do one of the following:
</p>
<p>
  <ul>
    <li>  
      <p>
        If the function is a composition of basic functions, state a formula for the inner function <m>g</m> and the outer function <m>f</m> so that the overall composite function can be written in the form <m>f(g(x))</m>.
      </p>  
    </li> 
    <li>
      <p>
        If the function is a sum, product, or quotient of basic functions, use the appropriate rule to determine its derivative.
      </p>
    </li>  
  </ul>  
</p>
<p>
    <ol marker="a." cols="2">
      <li>
        <p >
          <m>h(x) = \tan(2^x)</m>
        </p>

        <!-- Interactive Answers -->
        <p>
          Fundamental algebraic structure: 
          <choiceInput name='question2a' inline>
            <choice>Sum</choice>
            <choice>Product</choice>
            <choice>Quotient</choice>
            <choice>Composition</choice>
          </choiceInput>
        
          <answer name='question2aAnswer'><award><when>
            $question2a = Composition
          </when></award></answer>

          <conditionalContent>
            <case condition='$question2aAnswer.creditAchieved = 1'>
              <p> Inner function formula: <mathInput name='question2aInner'> </mathInput> 
              <answer><award><when>
                $question2aInner = 2^x
              </when></award></answer>
              </p>
              <p> Outer function formula: <mathInput name='question2aOuter'> </mathInput>
              <answer><award><when>
                $question2aOuter = tan(x)
              </when></award></answer>
              </p>
            </case>
          </conditionalContent>
          
        </p>
        <!-- End Interactive Answers -->
         
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          <m>p(x) = 2^x \tan(x)</m>
        </p>

<!-- Interactive Answers -->
          <p>
          Fundamental algebraic structure: 
          <choiceInput name='question2b' inline>
            <choice>Sum</choice>
            <choice>Product</choice>
            <choice>Quotient</choice>
            <choice>Composition</choice>
          </choiceInput>
          <answer name='question2bAnswer'><award><when>
            $question2b = Product
          </when></award></answer>

          <conditionalContent>
            <case condition='$question2bAnswer.creditAchieved = 1'>
              <p> For <m>p(x) = 2^x \tan(x)</m>, it follows that
              <m>p'(x) =</m> <mathInput name='question2bDerivative'> </mathInput> 
              <answer><award><when>
                $question2bDerivative = <derivative> 2^x * tan(x) </derivative>
              </when></award></answer>
              </p>
            </case>
          </conditionalContent>
          
        </p>
<!-- End Interactive Answers -->
      </li>

